22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a7eb4b788914e5551d5b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20UK-based%20firm%20Twig%20is%20bioengineering%20some%20of%20the%20ingredients%20found%20in%20margarine.%3Cp%3Etowfiqu%20ahamed%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EMany%20common%20consumer%20food%20products%20are%20derived%20from%20fossil%20fuels.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ESome%20companies%20are%20looking%20at%20ways%20to%20produce%20these%20products%20through%20other%20means.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EAI%20and%20computational%20biology%20are%20helping%20manufacturers%20produce%20alternatives%2C%20like%20cultivated%20animal-fat%20cells.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThis%20story%20is%20part%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fhow-emerging-tech-is-changing-everything%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHow%20Emerging%20Tech%20Is%20Changing%20Everything%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20a%20series%20exploring%20the%20transformative%20impact%20of%20tech%20innovations%20across%20industries.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMultinational%20consumer%20food%20brands%2C%20including%20the%20fast-food%20giants%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncl.ac.uk%2Fpress%2Farticles%2Flatest%2F2023%2F10%2Fconversationbigfoodcompanies%2F%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%20and%20Burger%20King%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20under%20increasing%20pressure%20to%20decarbonize%20their%20supply%20chains%20and%20meet%20global%20net-zero%20and%20ESG%20goals.%20Many%20common%20ingredients%20used%20in%20consumer%20products%20are%20derived%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20or%20produced%20through%20unsustainable%20farming%20methods.%20To%20slow%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20the%20transition%20to%20more%20sustainable%20production%20methods%20is%20necessary%2C%20but%20the%20methods%20in%20use%20now%20can%20be%20resource-intensive%20and%20costly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20pursuit%20of%20a%20more%20sustainable%20and%20environmentally%20friendly%20future%2C%20some%20companies%20are%20beginning%20to%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-promising-climate-tech-startups-vcs-2023-10%5C%22%3Eartificial%20intelligence%20and%20bioengineering%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20develop%20new%20food%20ingredients%20that%20may%20one%20day%20replace%20environmentally%20harmful%20substances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UK-based%20bioengineering%20firm%20Twig%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20using%20AI%20and%20robotics%20to%20create%20sustainable%20alternatives%20to%20ingredients%20derived%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20or%20intensive%20farming.%20These%20include%20ingredients%20like%20acetone%2C%20isoprene%2C%20and%20palmitic%20acid%2C%20which%20are%20found%20in%20everyday%20items%20such%20as%20margarines%2C%20paint%20strippers%2C%20cosmetics%2C%20soap%2C%20detergents%2C%20and%20more.%20Twig%20is%20working%20on%20replacements%20for%20these%20chemicals%20that%20would%20be%20created%20using%20bio-fermented%20bacteria%20cells.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20AI%20tells%20us%20how%20to%20make%20sustainable%2C%20bioidentical%20replacements%20using%20bio-fermented%20bacteria%20cells%2C%20reducing%20our%20impact%20on%20the%20planet%20and%20bringing%20supply%20chain%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20Russ%20Tucker%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Twig%2C%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAccelerating%20progress%20with%20AI%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20traditional%20bioengineering%20processes%2C%20it%20can%20take%20four%20to%2010%20years%20to%20develop%20a%20potential%20ingredient%20strain%2C%20which%20is%20often%20costly%20and%20there's%20no%20guarantee%20of%20success.%20Twig%20employs%20a%20software-driven%20approach%2C%20using%20a%20design-build-test%20cycle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwig's%20robotic%20platform%20automates%20the%20screening%20of%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20bacteria%20cells%2C%20generating%20large%20datasets%20in%20record%20time.%20This%20data%20is%20then%20analyzed%20to%20determine%20the%20most%20optimal%20and%20sustainable%20way%20to%20produce%20ingredients.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20we%20can%20be%2010%20times%20faster%20and%2010%20times%20cheaper%20than%20current%20commercial%20bioengineering%20approaches%2C%26quot%3B%20Tucker%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EToward%20sustainable%20alternatives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20meat%20industry%20is%20a%20major%20contributor%20to%20pollution%20and%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions.%20To%20address%20these%20environmental%20issues%2C%20sustainable%20alternatives%20are%20essential.%20Today%2C%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F3d-printed-vegan-salmon-hits-european-market-2023-10%5C%22%3Ealternative%20protein%3C%2Fa%3E%20products%20rely%20on%20plant-based%20oils%2C%20which%20lack%20the%20taste%20and%20cooking%20properties%20of%20traditional%20animal%20fats.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20production%20of%20palm%20oil%2C%20a%20common%20source%20of%20plant-based%20fats%2C%20presents%20its%20own%20sustainability%20challenges%20such%20as%20deforestation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoxton%20Farms%2C%20a%20London-based%20biotech%20company%2C%20is%20working%20on%20creating%20cultivated%20fat%20as%20a%20sustainable%20alternative%20to%20traditional%20animal%20fats.%20The%20company%20aims%20to%20make%20meat%20alternatives%20taste%20like%20the%20real%20thing%20by%20growing%20cruelty-free%2C%20sustainable%20animal%20fats%2C%20which%20would%20be%20combined%20with%20plant-based%20proteins.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20collect%20just%20a%20small%20sample%20of%20fat%20cells%20from%20a%20pig%20before%20growing%20them%20in%20a%20process%20called%20cell%20culturing%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ed%20Steele%2C%20the%20company's%20cofounder.%20%26quot%3BOver%20a%20few%20weeks%2C%20those%20cells%20multiply%2C%20grow%2C%20and%20we%20harvest%20juicy%2C%20cultivated%20fat%20cells.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20is%20essential%20in%20making%20cultivated%20meat%20commercially%20viable.%20Hoxton%20Farms'%20interdisciplinary%20approach%20combines%20computational%20biology%2C%20mathematical%20modeling%2C%20and%20machine%20learning%20to%20optimize%20the%20production%20process%20and%20customize%20taste%20and%20nutrition%20profiles.%20And%20the%20company%20says%20its%20approach%20allows%20it%20to%20achieve%20cost%20parity%20with%20plant%20oils%20at%20a%20commercial%20scale.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERegulatory%20challenges%20and%20the%20path%20forward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20potential%20for%20sustainable%20and%20alternative%20food%20products%20is%20promising%2C%20regulatory%20challenges%20exist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20a%20new%20ingredient%20is%20approved%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20manufacturers%20must%20navigate%20the%20Food%20Standards%20Agency's%20novel%20foods%20process%2C%20which%20can%20be%20long%20and%20bureaucratic%2C%20Steele%20said.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20Brexit%2C%20we%20retained%20EU%20law%20governing%20novel%20foods%20and%20inherited%20a%20process%20that%20is%20not%20fit%20for%20purpose.%26quot%3B%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20regulatory%20process%20in%20the%20US%20is%20not%20streamlined%3A%20The%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20regulates%20animal%20meat%2C%20and%20the%20Food%20and%20Drug%20Administration%20regulates%20plant-based%20meat%20alternatives.%20Cell-based%20meats%20are%20jointly%20regulated%20by%20the%20FDA%20and%20the%20USDA.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBringing%20this%20new%20tech%20to%20market%20could%20also%20face%20pushback%20from%20the%20food%20industry%2C%20which%20can%20complicate%20the%20approval%20and%20labeling%20process%20for%20alternative%20producers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20traditional%20protein%20industry%20is%20going%20a%20bit%20fake-news%20on%20alternative%20proteins%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Shivin%20Kohli%2C%20a%20senior%20manager%20at%20Access%20Partnership%2C%20a%20tech-policy%20advisory%20board.%20%26quot%3BThere%20have%20been%20challenges%20recently%20on%20calling%20alternative%20milks%20'milks.'%20This%20is%20because%20the%20dairy%20industry%20doesn't%20think%20they%20are%2C%20strictly%20speaking%2C%20milk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKohli%20said%20that%20argument%20%26quot%3Bseverely%20jeopardizes%20the%20consumer%20attractiveness%20of%20alternatives.%20If%20alternative%20proteins%20are%20having%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F2071-1050%2F14%2F22%2F15370%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eissues%20with%20consumer%20acceptance%3C%2Fa%3E%20already%2C%20can%20you%20imagine%20how%20bad%20it%20would%20be%20if%20Impossible%20couldn't%20call%20itself%20'meat'%3F%20Policy%20needs%20to%20be%20very%20clear%20about%20guardrailing%20this%20kind%20of%20pushback.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20administrations%20need%20to%20ensure%20a%20level%20playing%20field%2C%20Kohli%20said.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20is%20saying%20don't%20regulate%20novel%20proteins%20and%20ingredients%2C%20but%20don't%20expect%20there%20to%20be%20more%20onerous%20requirements%20than%20traditional%20proteins%20to%20just%20appease%20the%20big%20players%20such%20as%20for%20labeling%2C%20safety%2C%20and%20inspection.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-emerging-tech-transforming-food-production-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699390780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a7eb936d588dc55cc5f05%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-emerging-tech-transforming-food-production-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20companies%20are%20looking%20to%20get%20fossil%20fuels%20out%20of%20food%20production.%20They%20think%20AI%20and%20other%20emerging%20technologies%20are%20the%20answer.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Hazel%20Davis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUr