0stretch%2C%20with%20credit%20cards%20and%20student%20loans%20accounting%20for%20a%20significant%20portion.%20Credit%20card%20debt%20hit%20%241%20trillion%20for%20the%20first%20time%20ever%20this%20past%20summer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20increase%20in%20balances%20is%20consistent%20with%20strong%20nominal%20spending%20and%20real%20GDP%20growth%20over%20the%20same%20time%20frame%2C%26quot%3B%20Fed%20researchers%20wrote%20in%20an%20accompanying%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flibertystreeteconomics.newyorkfed.org%2F2023%2F11%2Fcredit-card-delinquencies-continue-to-rise-who-is-missing-payments%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20with%20the%20data.%20%26quot%3BBut%20credit%20card%20delinquencies%20continue%20to%20rise%20from%20their%20historical%20lows%20seen%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20have%20now%20surpassed%20pre-pandemic%20levels.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAggregate%20delinquency%20rates%20jumped%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Fed%20economists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20September%2C%203%25%20of%20outstanding%20debt%20had%20reached%20some%20stage%20of%20delinquency%2C%20an%20increase%20of%200.4%20percentage%20points%20from%20the%20prior%20quarter%2C%20though%20down%201.7%20percentage%20points%20from%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20in%202019%2C%20the%20stretch%20before%20the%20pandemic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClose%20to%209.5%25%20of%20credit%20card%20balances%20were%20more%20than%2090%20days%20delinquent%20last%20quarter%2C%20up%20from%208%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20and%207.6%25%20during%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221478%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Credit%20card%20balances%20and%20delinquency%20rates%20from%20the%20New%20York%20Fed%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a884136d588dc55cc6b92%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22941%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%