%20and%20add%20to%20the%20government's%20outstanding%20debt%2C%20investors%20are%20poised%20to%20worry%20about%20the%20lingering%20risks%20of%20inflation%2C%20bond%20defaults%2C%20and%20currency%20debasement%2C%20according%20to%20BofA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLikely%20central%20banks%20may%20simply%20bail%20out%20governments%20in%20coming%20years%20via%20quantitative%20easing%20and%20the%20introduction%20of%20yield%20curve%20control%20(policies%20that%20would%20be%20US%20dollar%20negative)%2C%26quot%3B%20Hartnett%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20separate%20measure%20of%20US%20debt%20that's%20more%20closely%20followed%20by%20economists%20is%20%26quot%3Bdebt%20held%20by%20the%20public%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20less%20daunting%20but%20still%20on%20a%20steep%20uptrend.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20fiscal%202023%2C%20it%20stood%20at%20%2426.3%20trillion%2C%20or%2098%25%20of%20projected%20GDP%2C%20and%20the%20CBO%20sees%20it%20climbing%20to%20115%25%20by%202033.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20if%20interest%20rates%20do%20fall%20and%20the%20federal%20deficit%20is%20contained%2C%20don't%20expect%20the%20federal%20government%20to%20ever%20stop%20borrowing%20money.%20US%20debt%20will%20always%20rise%20because%20it%20fuels%20economic%20growth%20and%20helps%20drive%20the%20circulation%20of%20money.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-the-free-bank-era-2013-2%5C%22%3Eone%20time%20the%20government%20did%20pay%20off%20all%20of%20its%20interest-bearing%20debts%20in%201835%2C%20a%20two-year%20depression%20shortly%20followed.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-debt-50-trillion-2033-federal-deficits-treasury-bond-crash-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699388485000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a8a8a3cc84b4dfafe04c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%2