DwB%2F%3Fimg_index%3D1%5C%22%3EInstagram%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20ptosis%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EPtosis%20is%20also%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bdrooping%20eyelid%26quot%3B.%20It%20is%20a%20medical%20condition%20characterised%20by%20the%20sagging%20or%20downward%20displacement%20of%20the%20upper%20eyelid.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aao.org%2Feye-health%2Fdiseases%2Fwhat-is-ptosis%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Academy%20of%20Ophthalmology%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20condition%20can%20affect%20one%20or%20both%20eyelids%20and%20can%20vary%20in%20severity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPtosis%20can%20also%20limit%20or%20even%20completely%20block%20normal%20vision.%20This%20condition%20can%20be%20caused%20by%20various%20factors%2C%20including%20age-related%20changes%2C%20muscle%20weakness%2C%20nerve%20damage%2C%20or%20congenital%20(present%20at%20birth)%20factors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESymptoms%20of%20ptosis%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.webmd.com%2Feye-health%2Fptosis%5C%22%3EWebMD%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20drooping%20eyelids%20that%20can%20obstruct%20the%20field%20of%20vision%20are%20one%20of%20the%20main%20symptoms.%20Fatigue%20or%20strain%20from%20continually%20lifting%20the%20eyelids%20to%20see%20clearly%20is%20another%20symptom.%20People%20suffering%20from%20this%20condition%20can%20also%20experience%20the%20uneven%20appearance%20of%20the%20eyes%2C%20with%20one%20eyelid%20drooping%20more.%20One%20may%20also%20experience%20difficulty%20keeping%20the%20eye%20open%2C%20especially%20when%20tired.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPtosis%20can%20cause%20problems%20when%20you%20drive%2C%20read%2C%20or%20even%20walk%20up%20and%20down%20stairs%2C%20as%20per%20WebMD.%20If%20you%20suspect%20you%20have%20ptosis%2C%20it's%20essential%20to%20consult%20with%20an%20eye%20specialist%20or%20ophthalmologist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699373700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fchrouovg_zeenat-aman_625x300_07_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fwhat-is-ptosis-the-eye-condition-zeenat-aman-has-been-battling-for-years-4555145%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Veteran%20actress%20Zeenat%20Aman%20on%20Tuesday%20opened%20up%20about%20a%20health%20condition%20she%20has%20been%20suffering%20from%20for%20four%20decades.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fwhat-is-ptosis-the-eye-condition-zeenat-aman-has-been-battling-for-years-4555145%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fwhat-is-ptosis-the-eye-condition-zeenat-aman-has-been-battling-for-years-4555145%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fwhat-is-ptosis-the-eye-condition-zeenat-aman-has-been-battling-for-years-4555145%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20Shocking%20Discovery%20Scientists%20Find%20Viruses%20Growing%20On%20Each%20Other%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EResearchers%20in%20the%20US%20have%20made%20a%20shocking%20discovery%20as%20they%20saw%20viruses%20latching%20onto%20each%20other.%20Two%20'Bacteriophage'%20viruses%20have%20used%20each%20other%20to%20help%20replicate.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20has%20ever%20seen%20a%20bacteriophage%20-%20or%20any%20other%20virus%20-%20attach%20to%20another%20virus%2C%26quot%3B%20lead%20study%20author%20Tagide%20deCarvalho%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20The%20study%20suggests%20there%20may%20be%20many%20more%20cases%20of%20this%20kind%20of%20relationship%20waiting%20to%20be%20discovered.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41396-023-01548-0%5C%22%3EInternational%20Society%20of%20Microbial%20Ecology%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20October%2031.%20The%20study%20explains%20when%20a%20satellite%20virus%20infiltrates%20a%20cell%2C%20it%20tries%20to%20rely%20on%20helper%20viruses%20in%20order%20to%20replicate%20their%20DNA.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Fhealth%2Fviruses-infections-disease%2Fin-world-1st-virus-spotted-attached-to-2nd-virus%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELive%20Science%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ereport%20says%20that%20the%20satellite%20and%20helper%20sometimes%20need%20to%20infect%20the%20same%20cell%20simultaneously%2C%20so%20they%20need%20to%20be%20close%20to%20each%20other%20during%20the%20process.%20However%2C%20the%20new%20research%20says%20that%20satellites%20actually%20attach%20themselves%20to%20a%20helper.%20It%20attaches%20itself%20to%20a%20virus%20%26quot%3Bneck%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20made%20this%20discovery%20by%20looking%20at%20environmental%20samples%20containing%20a%20family%20of%20bacteriophage%20satellites%20that%20infect%20Streptomyces%20bacteria.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20of%20the%20study%20analysed%20the%20genomes%20of%20these%20bacteriophages%20and%20their%20bacterial%20hosts.%20They%20soon%20discovered%20that%20the%20satellites%20had%20genes%20that%20coded%20for%20their%20outer%20protein%20shell%20but%20not%20the%20key%20genes%20needed%20to%20replicate%20within%20bacterial%20cells.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EExplaining%20why%20would%20the%20satellite%20grab%20the%20helper's%20neck%2C%20it%20says%20that%20some%20satellites%20lack%20a%20gene%20needed%20for%20them%20to%20integrate%20into%20the%20genome%20of%20bacterial%20host%20cells%20after%20entering%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20findings%20demonstrate%20an%20ever-increasing%20array%20of%20satellite%20strategies%20for%20genetic%20dependence%20on%20their%20helpers%20in%20the%20evolutionary%20arms%20race%20between%20satellite%20and%20helper%20phages%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote%20in%20the%20study.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20possible%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20bacteriophages%20that%20people%20thought%20were%20contaminated%20were%20actually%20these%20satellite-helper%20systems%2C%26quot%3B%20deCarvalho%20said%20in%20the%20statement.%20%26quot%3BSo%20now%2C%20with%20this%20paper%2C%20people%20might%20be%20able%20to%20recognize%20more%20of%20these%20systems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699373700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fq6fq9kg_virus-growing-on-each-other_625x300_07_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fin-shocking-discovery-scientists-find-viruses-growing-on-each-other-4555146%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20study%20was%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20of%20the%20International%20Society%20of%20Microbial%20Ecology%20on%20October%2031.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fin-shocking-discovery-scientists-find-viruses-growing-on-each-other-4555146%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fin-shocking-discovery-scientists-find-viruses-growing-on-each-other-4555146%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fin-shocking-discovery-scientists-find-viruses-growing-on-each-other-4555146%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Decoding%20People's%20Poll%20Pulse%20In%20Indore%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22The%20countdown%20to%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20Assembly%20polls%20has%20begun%2C%20As%20the%20state%20votes%20in%20a%20single%20phase%20on%20November%2017%2C%20NDTV%20takes%20on%20the%20election%20fever%20in%20Indore%20and%20decodes%20what%20is%20the%20poll%20pulse%20of%20the%20people.%20Watch%20The%20Last%20Word.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699373280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2F48lc5bak_the-last-word_640x480_07_November_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fshows%2Fthe-last-word%2Fmadhya-pradesh-assembly-polls-d