%206%2C%20days%20after%20she%20appeared%20before%20the%20ethics%20committee.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGiven%20her%20past%20history%20of%20filing%20fraudulent%20criminal%20complaints%20against%20me%20(24.03.2023%20and%2023.09.2023)%20and%20falsely%20alleging%20offences%20such%20as%20trespass%2C%20and%20criminal%20intimidation%2C%20and%20thereafter%20withdrawing%20the%20same%20in%20writing%20(on%2004.10.2023)%2C%20it%20is%20a%20grave%20cause%20for%20concern%20to%20me.%20There%20is%20every%20possibility%20that%20Smt.%20Moitra%20might%20intentionally%20come%20to%20my%20residential%20premises%20with%20the%20sole%20objective%20of%20filing%20further%20fraudulent%20complaints%20against%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mr%20Dehadrai%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Cause%20Of%20Concern'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Dehadrai%20was%20reportedly%20in%20a%20relationship%20with%20the%20Trinamool%20MP%20and%20they%20have%20allegedly%20not%20been%20on%20the%20best%20terms%20since%20they%20parted%20ways.%20One%20of%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20friction%20between%20them%20is%20their%20pet%20dog%2C%20a%20Rottweiler%20named%20Henry.%20Both%20have%20accused%20the%20other%20of%20'stealing'%20Henry%20and%20a%20battle%20for%20his%20custody%20is%20being%20fought%20in%20court.%20The%20dog%20is%20currently%20with%20Ms%20Moitra.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20previously%20informed%20the%20Commissioner%20of%20Police%2C%20Delhi%2C%20on%2019.10.2023%20and%20then%20on%2021.10.2023%20regarding%20these%20fraudulent%20and%20bogus%20complaints%20which%20Ms%20Moitra%20had%20foisted%20on%20me%20with%20the%20objective%20of%20using%20them%20as%20leverage%20to%20force%2Fcompel%20me%20to%20hand%20over%20the%20custody%20of%20my%20pet%20dog%2C%20and%20I%20have%20also%20flagged%20to%20the%20Commissioner%20the%20very%20serious%20threat%20to%20my%20life%20which%20I%20anticipate%20on%20account%20of%20the%20Complaints%20filed%20by%20me%20with%20CBI%20against%20Smt.%20Moitra%20and%20her%20associates%20%2F%20accomplices%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyer%20said%20that%2C%20in%20this%20context%2C%20her%20coming%20to%20his%20residence%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bgrave%20cause%20for%20concern%26quot%3B%20for%20him%20as%20it%20intimidates%20his%20staff.%20He%20also%20asked%20why%20someone%20who%20claimed%20an%20acrimonious%20past%20with%20him%20would%20go%20to%20his%20residence%20for%20two%20days%20in%20a%20row.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Dehadrai%20said%20he%20feared%20that%20the%20Trinamool%20MP%20was%20using%20Henry%20as%20an%20excuse%20to%20go%20to%20his%20residence%20to%20intimidate%20him.%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20she%20had%20filed%20various%20complaints%20against%20him%2C%20including%20a%20defamation%20case%20pending%20in%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%2C%20and%20said%20it%20was%20suspicious%20and%20inappropriate%20for%20her%20to%20show%20up%20at%20his%20house%20without%20any%20invitation%20or%20cause.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wish%20to%20make%20it%20absolutely%20clear%20that%20I%20have%20not%20invited%20Smt.%20Moitra%20to%20my%20residence%2C%20and%20that%20she%20has%20come%20uninvited%20and%20with%20a%20very%20apparent%20intention%20to%20commit%20trespass%20and%20to%20intimidate%20me.%20I%20have%20every%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20Ms%20Moitra%20and%20her%20close%20associate...%20are%20conspiring%20to%20cause%20physical%20harm%20to%20me%20as%20revenge%20for%20filing%20criminal%20complaints%20alleging%20corruption%20against%20them.%20I%20am%20requesting%20you%20once%20again%20to%20provide%20adequate%20security%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyer%20requested%20the%20police%20to%20investigate%20the%20matter%2C%20register%20a%20First%20Information%20Report%20against%20Ms%20Moitra%20and%20take%20necessary%20action%20against%20her%20for%20the%20alleged%20trespass%20and%20intimidation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20pertains%20to%20trespass%2C%20crimin