me%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FYP9AmTnWDZ8%3Fsi%3DBJ8SeMeJ3TVkaaTL%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApoorvanand%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Welcome%20to%20this%20series%20of%20the%20Nehru%20Dialogues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20this%20series%20to%20create%20a%20platform%20for%20dialogue.%20The%20only%20principle%20or%20value%20with%20which%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20can%20be%20associated%20is%20the%20principle%20of%20dialogue.%20A%20dialogue%20is%20not%20necessary%20only%20for%20consent%20or%20for%20people%20to%20agree%20with%20each%20other%2C%20but%20it%20should%20rather%20provide%20a%20space%20where%20people%20can%20disagree%2C%20and%20where%20there%20can%20be%20a%20dispute%2C%20but%20the%20intention%20is%20to%20understand%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Nehru%20Dialogues%20is%20not%20only%20limited%20to%20a%20discussion%20on%20Nehru%20or%20the%20aspects%20of%20his%20personality%20or%20what%20he%20has%20written%3B%20it%20revolves%20around%20the%20concerns%20he%20had.%20We%20try%20to%20talk%20and%20and%20through%20that%2C%20we%20can%20say%20that%20everything%20in%20this%20world%20falls%20under%20that%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20series%20consists%20of%20independent%20lectures%2C%20discussions%2C%20and%20panel%20discussions.%20We%20discuss%20books.%20Those%20books%20which%20deserve%20discussion%20are%20talked%20about.%20That%20means%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20just%20talk%20about%20sociology%20or%20literature%20or%20science%20or%20economics.%20We%20discuss%20every%20area%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20need%20to%20introduce%20Professor%20Satish%20Deshpande.%20All%20of%20you%20are%20familiar%20with%20him.%20Till%20now%20we%20consider%20him%20to%20be%20from%20Delhi%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20consider%20him%20in%20future%20too.%20Although%20he%20has%20said%20goodbye%20to%20Delhi%20and%20has%20now%20moved%20to%20Karnataka%2C%20you%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20think%20that%20it%20has%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20the%20Karnataka%20election%20results.%20Its%20only%20relation%20is%20that%20Deshpande%20was%20probably%20very%20fed%20up%20with%20the%20pollution%20of%20Delhi%20and%20went%20to%20Bengaluru%20to%20find%20clean%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDeshpande%20will%20speak%20with%20us%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20caste%20census.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20talk%20about%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20caste%20census%2C%20one%20of%20the%20many%20allegations%20against%20Nehru%20comes%20to%20the%20fore%20that%20he%20ignored%20the%20reality%20of%20caste%20and%20thought%20that%20if%20India%20transformed%20into%20a%20modern%20society%2C%20then%20the%20problem%20of%20caste%20would%20automatically%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20this%20is%20an%20allegation%20against%20him%20and%20there%20is%20a%20basis%20for%20it.%20But%20as%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20caste%20is%20still%20the%20biggest%20concrete%20reality%2C%20which%20cannot%20be%20ignored.%20But%20the%20most%20concrete%20truth%2C%20if%20we%20admit%20we%20want%20to%20understand%20it%2C%20is%20this%3A%20The%20biggest%20concrete%20truth%20is%20that%20you%20want%20to%20divide%20the%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fneed-of-the-hour-a-selfie-called-caste-census-india-must-confront-its-truth%5C%22%3ENeed%20of%20the%20Hour%3A%20A%20Selfie%20Called%20Caste%20Census%20%E2%80%93%20India%20Must%20Confront%20its%20Truth%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20firstly%2C%20what%20is%20the%20politics%20of%20this%20entire%20concept%20and%20the%20demand%20that%20is%20being%20made%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20what%20will%20it%20mean%20for%20democracy%20and%20what%20will%20be%20the%20consequences%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20Bihar%20conducted%20a%20caste%20census%20and%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20debate%20going%20on%20about%20it%20in%20sociology%20and%20politics.%20Satish%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20understand%20caste%20among%20social%20scientists%20and%20in%20the%20political%20field%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20is%20working%20on%20it%2C%20so%20we%20requested%20him%20to%20talk%20to%20us%20on%20this%20topic.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThank%20you%20very%20much%20Satish%20and%20all%20of%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESatish%20Deshpande%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EMany%20thanks%20to%20Apoorvanand%20%3Cem%3Eji.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20started%20from%20Nehru%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20so%20it%20is%20right%20that%20it%20should%20start%20from%20here.%20We%20are%20now%20aware%20that%20many%20allegations%20are%20being%20made%20against%20Nehru%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20they%20are%20being%20lobbed%20on%20his%20forehead.%20But%20this%20alleged%20fault%20is%20that%20he%20did%20not%20understand%20the%20subject%20of%20caste.%20I%20think%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20truth%20in%20this%20allegation.%20But%20I%20also%20believe%20that%20if%20he%20had%20been%20alive%20today%2C%20he%20would%20have%20had%20no%20hesitation%20in%20taking%20part%20in%20this%20debate.%20Perhaps%2C%20he%20would%20not%20have%20hesitated%20in%20admitting%20that%20he%20had%20made%20a%20mistake%20because%20today%20we%20would%20be%20okay%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20used%20to%20such%20leaders%20who%20never%20make%20any%20mistakes.%20So%2C%20if%20you%20have%20a%20leader%2C%20in%20any%20country%2C%20who%20is%20never%20making%20any%20mistakes%2C%20then%20you%20should%20be%20afraid%20because%20the%20times%20are%20not%20good.%20If%20a%20leader%20never%20makes%20any%20mistakes%2C%20then%20the%20situation%20is%20worrying.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20I%20will%20dwell%20on%20the%20question%20of%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20Nehru%20era%20regarding%20caste%2C%20due%20to%20which%20we%20are%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20where%20we%20are%20today.%20I%20am%20sorry%20I%20forgot%20to%20mention%20right%20at%20the%20beginning%20that%20in%20this%20linguistically%20diverse%20country%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20avoid%20a%20thinking%20that%20promotes%20one%20country%2C%20one%20language%2C%20one%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Feducation-policy-hindi-national-language%5C%22%3EIndia%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20Need%20Hindi%20to%20Unify%20the%20Masses%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20should%20not%20speak%20only%20in%20one%20language%20and%20there%20will%20be%20many%20people%20here%2C%20if%20not%20many%2C%20then%20at%20least%20some%20for%20whom%20Hindi%20is%20not%20a%20natural%20language.%20If%20it%20is%20not%20a%20natural%20language%2C%20then%20I%20will%20try%20to%20speak%20in%20English%20also%2C%20and%20today%2C%20in%202023%2C%20we%20should%20not%20shy%20away%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20English%20has%20evolved%20into%20an%20Indian%20language%20and%20it%20is%20language%20for%20communication.%20So%20that%E2%80%99s%20all%20on%20the%20question%20of%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrom%20time%20to%20time%20I%20will%20also%20speak%20in%20English%20and%20if%20someone%20interrupts%20me%20if%20I%20continue%20to%20speak%20in%20Hindi%2C%20I%20would%20like%20to%20put%20four%20proposals%20on%20caste%20enumeration%2C%20especially%20about%20casteism%2C%20before%20you%2C%20and%20then%20some%20question%20proposals.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20complexity%20lies%20in%20the%20question%20of%20casteism.%20So%2C%20we%20will%20try%20to%20settle%20it%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20proposal%20is%20that%20both%20counting%20and%20not%20counting%20castes%20are%20political%20steps%20in%20themselves.%20These%20are%20political%20decisions.%20Our%20instincts%20become%20our%20habits.%20Our%20common%20sense%20says%20that%20counting%20caste%20is%20purely%20political%2C%20but%20we%20cannot%20blame%20anyone%20for%20not%20counting%20it.%20In%20a%20way%2C%20we%20understand%20that%20there%20is%20no%20politics%20in%20this.%20This%20is%20beyond%20politics.%20It%20is%20wrong%20to%20believe%20so%20because%20not%20counting%20caste%20is%20as%20much%20a%20political%20decision%20and%20step%20as%20counting%20caste.%20I%20will%20talk%20about%20this%20in%20more%20detail.%20But%20my%20first%20proposal%20is%20that%20we%20should%20also%20recognise%20the%20politics%20of%20not%20counting%20caste%20and%20question%20it%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20politics%20of%20counting%20caste%20is%20good%2C%20questions%20are%20being%20asked%20about%20it.%20%5BIt%20is%5D%20always%20being%20done%20and%20this%20is%20also%20reasonable.%20They%20should%20also%20be%20questioned.%20But%20let%20us%20not%20assume%20that%20when%20we%20are%20not%20counting%20caste%2C%20we%20are%20beyond%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20rose%20just%20as%20Yudhishthira%E2%80%99s%20carriage%20is%20said%20to%20have%20moved%20above%20the%20ground.%20Secondly%2C%20I%20propose%20that%20Apoorvanand%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20already%20said%20it%20in%20his%20foreword.%20This%20is%20an%20old%20myth%20which%20we%20have%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20today%20that%20counting%20castes%20will%20lead%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20casteism%20and%20vice%20versa%2C%20although%20it%20is%20true%20that%20the%20process%20itself%20will%20increase%20awareness%20%5Bamong%20the%20masses%5D.%20We%20will%20talk%20about%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20later%2C%20but%20let%20us%20first%20assume%20that%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20count%20castes%2C%20then%20the%20notion%20that%20casteism%20will%20disappear%20is%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20after%2070%20years%20of%20independence%2C%20we%20should%20not%20have%20to%20repeat%20the%20same%20concept%20%5Bthat%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20count%20castes%2C%20then%20casteism%20will%20disappear%5D.%20Castes%20will%20continue%20to%20cast%20its%20shadow.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20third%20proposal%20also%20challenges%20our%20common%20notion.%20It%20says%20that%20we%20should%20not%20count%20caste%20surveys%20as%20a%20solution%20to%20any%20kind%20of%20issue%20or%20an%20achievement%20or%20a%20benefit%20of%20any%20kind%2C%20like%20counting%20the%20number%20of%20beneficiaries%20either%20in%20a%20single-engine%20or%20in%20a%20double-engine-governed%20state.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20means%20to%20an%20end.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20key%20to%20any%20solution%2C%20not%20a%20missing%20piece%20of%20a%20puzzle.%20It%E2%80%99s%20rather%20a%20small%20step%20towards%20a%20long%20journey.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20fourth%20solution%20towards%20the%20caste%20census%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20one%20conducted%20in%20Bihar%20recently%20which%20is%20referred%20to%20as%20a%20survey%20due%20to%20legal%20obligations%2C%20is%20that%20only%20counting%20the%20number%20of%20castes%20will%20be%20counterproductive%20if%20the%20process%20stops%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20important%20to%20understand%20the%20socio-economic%20factors.%20It%20will%20help%20us%20in%20understanding%20its%20place%20and%20meaning%20in%20society.%20Only%20counting%20will%20lead%20to%20a%20sense%20of%20hollow%20pride%20stopping%20any%20kind%20of%20progressive%20politics%20in%20its%20tracks.%20All%20of%20our%20governments%20since%20Independence%20have%20failed%20on%20this%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20state%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20a%20census%20of%20such%20a%20kind%20had%20been%20undertaken%20a%20long%20time%20ago%20but%20the%20results%20have%20not%20been%20published.%20The%20first%20unofficial%20survey%20of%20such%20kind%20was%20undertaken%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20but%20its%20results%20were%20not%20made%20public.%20We%20should%20applaud%20the%20Bihar%20government%20for%20making%20the%20preliminary%20findings%20public%2C%20but%20%5Bin%20my%20opinion%5D%2C%20they%20would%20fail%20%5Bin%20this%20matter%5D%20if%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20disclose%20the%20socio-economic%20conditions%20to%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20were%20my%20four%20proposals%20concerning%20the%20caste%20survey.%20I%20wanted%20to%20begin%20with%20these%20four%20propositions%20on%20the%20first%20meaningful%20term%20in%20the%20title%20which%20is%20%E2%80%98counting%E2%80%99%20%5Bof%20caste%5D.%20These%20are%20more%20or%20less%20familiar%20to%20most%20of%20us%2C%20so%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20think%20too%20hard%20about%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20proposition%20is%20that%20both%20the%20%E2%80%98counting%E2%80%99%20of%20caste%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98not%20counting%E2%80%99%20of%20caste%20are%20equally%20political.%20We%20are%20habituated%20to%20think%20of%20the%20counting%20of%20caste%20as%20obviously%20inherently%20and%20often%20pejoratively%20political%2C%20and%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20we%20think%20that%20not%20counting%20caste%20is%20somehow%20not%20political%20or%20above%20politics.%20That%20%5Bthis%20mindset%5D%20is%20simply%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENot%20counting%20caste%20is%20as%20much%20a%20political%20step%20as%20counting%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20second%20proposition%20is%20that%20it%20is%20high%20time%20we%20got%20rid%20of%20an%20old%20myth%20that%20not%20counting%20caste%20will%20reduce%20caste%20consciousness%20or%20casteism.%20The%2070%20years%20of%20our%20history%20of%20independence%20should%20show%20very%20clearly%20that%20this%20is%20not%20the%20case%20and%20that%20the%20caste%20groups%20that%20have%20been%20most%20effective%20in%20intervening%20in%20national-level%20Indian%20politics%20have%20been%20the%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBCs)%2C%20who%20have%20never%20officially%20been%20counted.%20So%20not%20counting%20caste%20is%20not%20going%20to%20lead%20to%20any%20lessening%20of%20caste%20consciousness%2C%20assuming%20that%20caste%20consciousness%20is%20something%20that%20should%20be%20gotten%20rid%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20third%20proposition%20is%20that%20we%20should%20get%20out%20of%20the%20habit%20of%20thinking%20of%20the%20caste%20census%20as%20some%20kind%20of%20a%20solution%20to%20a%20problem%2C%20as%20an%20achievement%2C%20or%20as%20some%20kind%20of%20a%20welfare%20good.%20%5BWe%20should%20not%20think%20of%20it%20as%5D%20something%20that%20is%20a%20product%20or%20a%20good%20or%20a%20benefit.%20So%2C%20counting%20caste%20is%20only%20a%20means%20to%20an%20end%2C%20it%20is%20not%20an%20end%20in%20itself%2C%20and%20it%20is%20best%20thought%20of%20as%20the%20first%20small%20step%20in%20a%20very%20long%20journey%20that%20we%20have%20to%20take%20on%20caste.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ffull-text-bihar-caste-survey-highlights-marginalised-micro-communities-bjp-faces-electoral-dilemma%5C%22%3EFull%20Text%3A%20Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%20Highlights%20Marginalised%20Micro-Communities%3B%20BJP%20Faces%20Electoral%20Dilemma%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20my%20fourth%20proposition%20on%20the%20counting%20of%20caste%20is%20that%20if%20one%20only%20counts%20caste%20names%2C%20then%20the%20population%20of%20castes%20tells%20us%20nothing%20about%20their%20social%20or%20economic%20status%2C%20which%20is%20what%20we%20are%20interested%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20%5Bcounting%5D%20exercise%20stops%20at%20this%20point%2C%20then%20this%20will%20end%20as%20a%20reactionary%20exercise%2C%20because%20simply%20counting%20the%20names%20won%E2%80%99t%20tell%20us%20about%20their%20social%20or%20economic%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20not%20interested%20in%20simply%20knowing%20the%20caste%20names.%20We%20are%20interested%20in%20what%20membership%20in%20caste%20means%20in%20social%2C%20political%20and%20economic%20terms%20today.%20This%20is%20the%20meaningful%20information%20that%20is%20required%20%5Bto%20be%20made%20public%5D.%20If%20that%20does%20not%20come%20out%20in%20a%20caste%20census%2C%20then%20the%20census%20is%20not%20a%20piece%20of%20progressive%20politics.%20It%20will%20feel%20like%20a%20dead%20end%20politics%20of%20identity%20that%20will%20ultimately%20reach%20nowhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENow%20I%20am%20moving%20on%20to%20%5Bmaking%5D%20some%20claims%2C%20propositions%2C%20and%20questions%20on%20the%20second%20main%20question%20in%20our%20title%20and%20the%20main%20word%20in%20our%20title%2C%20which%20is%20to%20do%20with%20casteism%20or%20%3Cem%3Ejatiyatavaad%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20now%2C%20I%20will%20present%20some%20proposals%2F%20propositions%20about%20casteism.%20Think%20of%20them%20as%20proposals%2Fquestions.%20This%20issue%20is%20bigger%20than%20the%20census%20itself%20and%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20enough%20about%20them%20and%20we%20haven%E2%80%99t%20given%20these%20questions%20much%20thought%20or%20nuance%20but%20the%20time%20has%20come%20to%20correct%20our%20course%20and%20try%20to%20understand%20these%20issues.%20So%20my%20first%20proposal%20is%E2%80%A6.and%20we%20could%20think%20of%20it%20as%20a%20question%2C%20so%20my%20first%20question%20is%2C%20what%20is%20casteism%3F%20What%20do%20we%20understand%20by%20this%20word%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20me%2C%20it%20not%20only%20exists%20covertly%20but%20also%20overtly.%20We%20are%20used%20to%20calling%20someone%20arrogant%20about%20their%20caste%20identity%20or%20someone%20who%20flaunts%20or%20shows%20off%20their%20caste%20every%20minute%20or%20exercises%20their%20privilege.%20We%20are%20used%20to%20these%20conditions.%20Does%20it%20not%20occur%20in%20other%20forms%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20me%2C%20in%20our%20country%2C%20the%20most%20glaring%20issue%20we%20face%20regarding%20caste%20is%20that%20another%20form%20of%20casteism%20exists%20which%20we%20cannot%20discern%20at%20first%20glance.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I%20have%20been%20using%20the%20word%20invisible%20for%20it%2C%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98invisible%20implies%E2%80%99%20acquits%20us%20of%20our%20role%20in%20its%20propagation%2C%20which%20is%20wrong.%20The%20covertness%20of%20casteism%20which%20I%20am%20talking%20about%20has%20been%20invisiblised%20by%20us%20only.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20natural%20characteristic%20and%20we%20have%20channelised%20this%20thought%20process%20through%20social%20conditioning%20across%20generations.%20The%20way%20it%E2%80%99s%20ignored%20or%20the%20failure%20to%20recognise%20these%20while%20being%20practised%20under%20our%20noses%20is%20also%20a%20result%20of%20such%20a%20condition.%20The%20way%20we%20socialise%20has%20created%20such%20a%20situation%20that%20we%20fail%20to%20understand%20it%20as%20casteism.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20we%20must%20understand%20that%20casteism%20is%20not%20only%20showing%20off%20or%20flouting%20one%E2%80%99s%20identity%20but%20also%20the%20social%20system%20that%20allows%20these%20practices%20to%20exist.%20Shouldn%E2%80%99t%20we%20call%20these%20a%20form%20of%20casteism%2C%20too%2C%20albeit%20slogans%20are%20not%20being%20shouted%2C%20and%20people%20are%20not%20rallying%20on%20the%20roads%3F%20But%20the%20effects%20of%20this%20system%20is%20that%20some%20castes%20are%20being%20taken%20advantage%20of%20regularly%2C%20which%20seems%20natural%20to%20us%2C%20which%20seems%20regular%20and%20ordinary%2C%20which%20in%20English%20is%20referred%20to%20as%20normalisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Hindi%2C%20when%20people%20ask%2C%20how%20much%20sugar%20would%20one%20like%2C%20people%20respond%20with%20%E2%80%9Cnormal%E2%80%9D.%20So%2C%20normal%20is%20something%20that%20is%20neither%20excessive%20nor%20lacking%20and%20subsequently%20becomes%20invisible.%20This%20is%20why%20we%20haven%E2%80%99t%20been%20able%20to%20solve%20this%20puzzle%20of%20caste.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEnglish%20is%20a%20very%20twisted%20language.%20Several%20words%20have%20silent%20letters%20but%20we%20still%20write%20them.%20We%20write%20%E2%80%98talk%E2%80%99.%20Here%20the%20letter%20%E2%80%98l%E2%80%99%20has%20no%20pronunciation.%20The%20same%20is%20the%20case%20with%20%E2%80%98walk%E2%80%99.%20Similarly%2C%20when%20talking%20about%20caste%2C%20we%20are%20mostly%20talking%20about%20the%20%E2%80%98lower%E2%80%99%20caste%20but%20this%20%E2%80%98lower%E2%80%99%20becomes%20silent.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20celebrated%20the%20fact%20that%20with%20the%20Modi%20government%20coming%20into%20power%2C%20caste%20politics%20has%20been%20sidelined.%20Here%20caste%20politics%20meant%20the%20politics%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98lower%E2%80%99%20castes.%20Since%202014%2C%20we%20have%20gone%20back%20to%20the%20time%20when%20politics%20revolved%20around%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste.%20Caste%20politics%20is%20still%20at%20play%20but%20the%20strata%20are%20different%20now.%20This%20is%20an%20even%20bigger%20problem%20as%20this%20lays%20the%20foundation%20for%20our%20cognitive%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20of%20our%20country%20with%20caste%20is%20that%20some%20questions%20have%20become%20hypervisible.%20One%20type%20of%20caste%20politics%20has%20gained%20prominence%20while%20the%20other%20one%2C%20which%20has%20been%20systemically%20underplayed%2C%20remains%20out%20of%20our%20purview.%20Our%20cognitive%20vision%20is%20asymmetrical.%20Caste%20is%20a%20puzzle%20that%20we%20are%20unable%20to%20solve.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20me%2C%20the%20caste%20survey%20is%20the%20first%20step%20towards%20the%20long%20journey%20of%20solving%20the%20puzzle%20of%20invisibility%20and%20hypervisibility%20in%20our%20society.%20Our%20approach%20towards%20this%20problem%20is%20lending%20to%20its%20rise.%20For%20this%2C%20we%20must%20refrain%20from%20this%20mentality%20of%20being%20pulled%20back%20to%20the%2019th%20century%20with%20caste%20politics.%20It%20is%20common%20to%20hear%20from%20people%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20not%20bothered%20by%20caste.%20We%20owe%20our%20everything%20to%20merit%20and%20not%20caste.%E2%80%9D%20They%20are%20not%20lying%20or%20being%20cunning.%20They%20genuinely%20believe%20in%20this.%20But%20we%20ask%20ourselves%20how%20society%20has%20empowered%20them%20to%20believe%20this%20notion%20of%20merit%20and%20not%20caste.%20I%20used%20to%20belong%20to%20the%20same%20tribe.%20I%20never%20associated%20with%20any%20caste%20pride%20and%20even%20revolted%20against%20my%20family%20when%20they%20tried%20to%20push%20caste%20in%20my%20life.%20But%20we%20can%20never%20choose%20to%20have%20or%20not%20have%20caste.%20It%20is%20a%20societal%20set-up.%20You%20may%20not%20talk%20about%20your%20caste%20but%20your%20caste%20will%20speak%20and%20when%20caste%20speaks%20everybody%20understands.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20banner%20of%20merit%2C%20we%20tend%20to%20avoid%20the%20banner%20of%20caste.%20This%20has%20been%20made%20possible%20in%20the%20Nehruvian%20era.%20In%20this%20era%2C%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20was%20empowered%20with%20resources%20to%20transform%20their%20caste%20capital%20into%20merit%20capital.%20In%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%2C%20the%20enthusiasm%20for%20independence%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20dialled%20down%2C%20nor%20had%20its%20idealism.%20The%20notion%2C%20that%20development%20can%20solve%20anything%2C%20was%20in%20the%20breeze.%20This%20was%20propagated%20primarily%20by%20Nehru.%20He%20stressed%20development%2C%20advancement%2C%20science%20and%20technology.%20He%20believed%20that%20this%20could%20solve%20the%20issue%20of%20caste.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20started%20inclining%20towards%20big%20industries%20due%20to%20its%20schemes%20after%20the%20second%20five-year%20plan.%20The%20demand%20for%20technically%20professional%20people%20increased.%20IITs%20were%20opened%20in%20the%20late%2050s%20and%20early%2060s%20and%20provided%20A-grade%20knowledge%20for%20almost%20free.%20These%20IITs%20created%20new%20professionals%20who%20got%20government%20jobs.%20The%20government%20was%20not%20only%20providing%20education%20at%20a%20nominal%20fee%20but%20also%20good%20jobs.%20This%20was%20emancipating%20the%20social%20status%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Nehruvian%20era%20leveraged%20social%20mobility.%20We%20cannot%20call%20it%20an%20unexpected%20outcome%20but%20at%20least%20it%20did%20not%20intend%20to%20empower%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20to%20transform%20its%20caste-based%20capital%20to%20merit%20capital.%20However%2C%20this%20was%20the%20result%20and%20I%20am%20a%20beneficiary%20of%20it.%20My%20grandfather%20was%20a%20landowner%20under%20his%20caste.%20He%20was%20able%20to%20sell%20off%20his%20land%20and%20send%20my%20father%20to%20an%20engineering%20college.%20He%20possessed%20land%20because%20of%20the%20caste%20strata%20he%20belonged%20to.%20He%20was%20able%20to%20buy%20knowledge%20for%20his%20son%20from%20that%20piece%20of%20land.%20And%20my%20father%20became%20an%20engineer%20and%20was%20employed%20in%20a%20government%20job.%20The%20difficulty%20starts%20with%20the%20next%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20childhood%20was%20spent%20in%20the%20Nehruvian%20era.%20We%20were%20surrounded%20by%20engineers%20and%20steel%20plants.%20They%20belonged%20to%20different%20Indian%20states%20but%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20realise%20that%20they%20belonged%20to%20a%20particular%20caste.%20We%20were%20just%20able%20to%20make%20out%20that%20they%20were%20Maharashtrian%20or%20Malayalam.%20But%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20that%20they%20were%20all%20Brahmins.%20Maybe%20the%20women%20had%20an%20idea%20but%20it%20was%20never%20addressed%20publicly.%20This%20is%20why%20I%20thought%20that%20I%20was%20not%20associated%20with%20caste.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fthe-role-of-intellectuals-in-the-anti-caste-movement-lessons-from-ambedkars-academic-credentials%5C%22%3EThe%20Role%20of%20Intellectuals%20in%20the%20Anti-caste%20Movement%3A%20Lessons%20From%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20Academic%20Credentials%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20got%20the%20opportunity%20to%20go%20to%20good%20schools%20and%20colleges%20where%20I%20earned%20merit.%20I%20believe%20in%20merit%20but%20it%20is%20not%20natural.%20By%20nature%2C%20merit%20may%20differ%20from%20person%20to%20person%2C%20but%20there%20is%20a%20difference%20in%20the%20way%20by%20which%20this%20merit%20is%20whetted.%20There%20is%20a%20huge%20inequality%20here%2C%20which%20is%20why%20a%20person%20like%20me%20overlooks%20caste%20and%20believes%20solely%20in%20merit.%20A%20person%20like%20me%20would%20believe%20that%20those%20asking%20for%20reservations%20are%20begging.%20They%20are%20lazy%20and%20do%20not%20believe%20in%20hard%20work.%20This%20story%20is%20not%20new%20and%20we%20have%20witnessed%20it%20very%20closely.%20I%20want%20to%20bring%20you%20to%20the%20conclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20conclusion%20is%20that%20dialogue%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20caste%20becomes%20impossible.%20This%20is%20because%20people%20like%20me%20believe%20that%20they%20have%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20caste.%20The%20role%20played%20by%20caste%20in%20making%20me%20what%20I%20am%20is%20perpetually%20ignored%20by%20me%20and%20even%20others.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20some%20people%20will%20not%20get%20anything%20unless%20they%20proclaim%20their%20caste.%20This%20makes%20the%20dialogue%20between%20these%20two%20groups%20very%20difficult.%20Thus%2C%20solving%20this%20issue%20within%20the%20democratic%20framework%20becomes%20impossible.%20We%20owe%20this%20%E2%80%98Great%20Transformation%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20Nehruvian%20era.%20This%20era%20provided%20one%20group%20with%20the%20means%20of%20modernising%20their%20caste%20capital%20while%20forcing%20the%20other%20group%20to%20identify%20themselves%20with%20their%20caste%20to%20receive%20any%20kind%20of%20benefit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20merit%20was%20being%20distributed%2C%20some%20were%20forced%20to%20disappear%20while%20others%20got%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share.%20This%20privileged%20lot%20refuses%20to%20believe%20that%20their%20merit%20has%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20their%20caste.%20This%20has%20made%20dialogue%20on%20this%20issue%20impossible.%20The%20only%20way%20to%20come%20out%20of%20this%20is%20to%20make%20this%20section%20of%20people%20believe%20in%20the%20omnipresence%20of%20their%20caste.%20A%20caste%20census%20is%20a%20kind%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fneed-of-the-hour-a-selfie-called-caste-census-india-must-confront-its-truth%5C%22%3Ecollective%20selfie%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20some%20believe%20that%20they%20do%20not%20have%20a%20caste%20while%20others%20hold%20a%20contrary%20belief.%20To%20begin%20the%20dialogue%2C%20we%20need%20to%20ask%2C%20%E2%80%98What%20is%20your%20caste%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20right%20to%20conduct%20a%20caste%20census%20lies%20with%20the%20government.%20This%20is%20the%20only%20survey%20where%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%20even%20begin%20to%20imagine%20someone%20else%20having%20an%20answer.%20We%20cannot%20ask%20this%20question%20in%20person%2C%20but%20failure%20to%20answer%20in%20a%20census%20can%20lead%20to%20imprisonment%2C%20because%20it%20is%20a%20legal%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20right%20to%20exercise%20it%20only%20belongs%20to%20the%20government.%20Therefore%2C%20if%20you%20are%20asked%20about%20caste%20during%20a%20census%2C%20then%20you%20are%20free%20to%20answer%20that%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20belong%20to%20any%20but%20there%20should%20be%20an%20answer%20nonetheless.%20You%20cannot%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CThink%20of%20it%20like%20an%20ordinary%20situation%20where%20you%20ask%20an%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20person%2C%20particularly%20men%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20is%20your%20caste%3F%E2%80%9D%20and%20he%20answers%20%E2%80%9CDon%E2%80%99t%20you%20know%20who%20I%20am%E2%80%9D.%20You%20cannot%20answer%20an%20enumerator%20in%20the%20same%20way.%20Maybe%20he%20knows%20but%20he%20has%20to%20ask%20the%20question.%20This%20process%20might%20not%20ensure%20a%20change%20of%20heart%20or%20guide%20us%20towards%20heaven%2C%20but%20this%20small%20step%20is%20something%20we%20must%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20let%20us%20come%20to%20the%20last%20and%20most%20complicated%20issue%20which%20is%20that%20if%20we%20mix%20caste%20and%20census%2C%20we%20will%20return%20to%20the%20core%20issue%20of%20numbers%2F%20population%2C%20because%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20about%20keeping%20count%20and%20counting%20and%20what%20will%20this%20step%20lead%20to%20a%20figure%2C%20perhaps.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20has%20this%20figure%20got%20to%20do%20with%20democracy%3F%20It%E2%80%99s%20very%20important%20to%20ask%20this%20question%20today%20because%20as%20we%20know%2C%20we%20are%20facing%20a%20multitude%20of%20questions%20such%20as%20how%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20questioned%20%5BCongress%20leader%5D%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20about%20the%20participation%20of%20politicians%20proportionate%20to%20the%20population%20and%20diverted%20the%20narrative%20to%2080%25%20Hindu%20population%20and%20their%20claim%20to%20participation.%20We%20should%20be%20wary%20of%20such%20a%20narrative%20of%20this%20union%20between%20numbers%20and%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20caste%20survey%20will%20highlight%20the%20numbers%20but%20if%20only%20a%20numerical%20value%20is%20highlighted%2C%20then%20that%20may%20be%20counterproductive.%20If%20other%20parameters%20such%20as%20social%20and%20economic%20conditions%20are%20factored%20in%2C%20then%20it%20will%20be%20progressive%20as%20it%20will%20allow%20us%20to%20identify%20the%20conditions%20of%20a%20particular%20caste%20at%20present%20and%20its%20participation%20in%20power%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20question%20is%2C%20are%20we%20not%20reducing%20our%20politics%20to%20a%20numeric%20value%3F%20Of%20course%2C%20it%20is%20a%20looming%20condition%20that%20scares%20us%20but%20it%20should%20not%20stop%20us%20from%20counting%20caste.%20This%2C%20according%20to%20me%2C%20will%20also%20mean%20taking%20a%20step%20backwards.%20We%20have%20to%20face%20this%20challenge%20because%20the%20steps%20that%20are%20being%20taken%20at%20the%20ground%20level%2C%20%5Bor%5D%20what%20we%20are%20witnessing%20during%20the%20election%2C%20the%20vote%20bank%20that%20emerges%20out%20of%20caste%20identity%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20this%20is%20a%20lazy%20concept%20to%20me%2C%20because%20it%20implies%20one%20will%20vote%20for%20a%20particular%20party%20attested%20to%20this%20identity%20which%20has%20never%20happened%20since%201952.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EM.N.%20Srinivas%2C%20who%20coined%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cvote%20bank%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20that%20the%20zamindars%20he%20spoke%20to%20doubted%20the%20loyalty%20of%20their%20servants%20regarding%20their%20voting%20choices%2C%20or%20if%20they%20voted%20according%20to%20their%20instructions.%20So%2C%20vote%20bank%20is%20not%20something%20that%20guarantees%20that%20the%20number%20%5Bof%20castes%5D%20will%20translate%20or%20transform%20into%20politics.%20Vote%20bank%20tries%20to%20scrap%20out%20the%20politics%20out%20of%20the%20politics%20itself%20and%20turns%20it%20into%20an%20automatic%20process%20where%20people%20are%20told%20to%20vote%20in%20accordance%20with%20their%20identity.%20This%20is%20obviously%20not%20possible%20as%20the%20socio-economic%20divisions%20get%20overlooked%20when%20we%20are%20only%20focused%20on%20numbers%2C%20like%20the%20internal%20disparities%20that%20exist%20within%20different%20groups%20belonging%20to%20OBCs%20you%20are%20aware%20of.%20This%20kind%20of%20disparity%20exists%20in%20every%20community.%20Highlighting%20these%20disparities%20and%20their%20amalgamation%20into%20politics%20is%20very%20important%20to%20us%2C%20so%20that%20we%20can%20move%20on%20from%20identity%20politics%20towards%20welfare%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20side%20of%20welfare%20politics%20lies%20the%20politics%20of%20justice%2C%20which%20will%20take%20a%20long%20time%20to%20achieve%2C%20but%20the%20counting%20of%20caste%20is%20our%20first%20step%20as%20we%20embark%20on%20this%20long%20journey.%20This%20may%20seem%20far-fetched%20that%20we%20will%20reach%20there%20if%20we%20conduct%20a%20caste%20survey%20but%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20do%20the%20counting%2C%20then%20we%20will%20never%20reach%20the%20destination.%20So%2C%20I%20believe%20if%20we%20are%20to%20touch%20the%20ideal%20image%20of%20a%20democracy%2C%20and%20who%20knows%20if%20anyone%20has%20ever%20been%20there%2C%20these%20are%20all%20unanswered%20questions%2C%20but%20if%20we%20are%20to%20proceed%20towards%20that%20direction%2C%20our%20first%20step%20should%20be%20to%20eradicate%20the%20roadblock%20parity%20that%20exists%20in%20our%20society%20and%20ask%20every%20citizen%20%E2%80%9Cwhat%20is%20your%20caste%E2%80%9D.%20Therefore%2C%20this%20caste%20survey%20is%20the%20only%20way%20to%20tackle%20not%20only%20overt%20casteism%20but%20also%20covert%20casteism%20according%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EApoorvanand%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThank%20you%20so%20much%20Satish%20and%20thanks%20to%20all%20of%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranscribed%20and%20translated%20from%20Hindi%20to%20English%20by%20Debarun%20Choudhury.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699358435000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F07173140%2Fshane-rounce-DNkoNXQti3c-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fhow-true-is-the-claim-that-bihar-caste-survey-is-promoting-casteism%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'This%20caste%20survey%20is%20the%20only%20way%20to%20tackle%20not%20only%20overt%20casteism%20but%20also%20covert%20casteism%2C'%20says%20professor%20Satish%20Deshpande%2C%20who%20talks%20about%20the%20implications%20of%20the%20recently%20conducted%20caste%20survey%20in%20Bihar.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fhow-true-is-the-claim-that-bihar-caste-survey-is-promoting-casteism%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UK's%20Sunak%20sets%20out%20pre-election%20agenda%20in%20King's%20Speech%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699358171000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fpho