itle%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699355751000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F07162541%2FKT-7-Nov-2023-B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-as-israel-escalates-attacks-on-gaza-has-blinkens-diplomacy-failed%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Karan%20Thapar%20interviews%20Hanan%20Ashrawi%2C%20a%20former%20higher%20education%20minister%20in%20the%20Palestine%20Authority.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-as-israel-escalates-attacks-on-gaza-has-blinkens-diplomacy-failed%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Two%20IAS%20Officers%20Chaperoned%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Bill%20Despite%20RBI's%20Objections%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F07155525%2FUntitled-design-5.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20finished%20hearing%20arguments%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20will%20hopefully%20deliver%20a%20judgment%20soon.%20I%20say%20hopefully%20because%20it%20has%20now%20been%20six%20years%20since%20the%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%202017%20Budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMany%20readers%20will%20not%20know%20the%20background%20to%20the%20bonds%20and%20what%20they%20are.%20In%20brief%2C%20it%20allows%20unlimited%2C%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20any%20registered%20political%20party.%20The%20scheme%20also%20allows%20anyone%2C%20including%20foreign%20governments%2C%20criminal%20gangs%20and%20of%20course%20corporate%20interests%2C%20the%20ability%20to%20influence%20political%20parties%20because%20parties%20could%20accept%20money%20without%20revealing%20who%20gave%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20to%20fund%20a%20party%20anonymously%20was%20made%20easy.%20Bonds%20would%20be%20available%20in%20denominations%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%201%20crore%20at%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20branches%20in%2029%20cities.%20A%20donor%20could%20purchase%20them%20through%20their%20bank%20account%20and%20hand%20them%20over%20to%20the%20party%20or%20individual%20of%20their%20choice%2C%20who%20could%20encash%20them.%20They%20would%20be%20valid%20for%2015%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20should%20alert%20us%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20something%20was%20off%20from%20the%20start.%20Four%20days%20before%20Budget%202017%2C%20a%20bureaucrat%20spotted%20the%20scheme%20in%20then%20finance%20minister%20Arun%20Jaitley%E2%80%99s%20speech%2C%20and%20noted%20that%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20assent%20was%20required.%20This%20was%20because%20the%20introduction%20of%20bonds%20required%20changes%20to%20the%20RBI%20Act%2C%20something%20that%20the%20government%20apparently%20did%20not%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-sc-questions-anonymity-of-electoral-bonds-and-voters-right-to-information%5C%22%3ESC%20Questions%20Anonymity%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20and%20Voters%E2%80%99%20Right%20to%20Information%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20officer%20drafted%20a%20proposed%20amendment%20to%20align%20the%20law%20with%20the%20change%20and%20sent%20the%20file%20up%20the%20ranks%20for%20the%20finance%20minister%20to%20see.%20The%20same%20day%2C%20January%2028%2C%202017%2C%20a%20Saturday%2C%20the%20RBI%20was%20sent%20a%20five-line%20email%20seeking%20its%20comments.%20The%20reply%20came%20on%20Monday%2C%20January%2030.%20The%20RBI%20said%20it%20was%20a%20bad%20idea%20as%20it%20went%20against%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20authority%20as%20the%20sole%20issuer%20of%20bearer%20instruments%2C%20meaning%20cash.%20These%20bonds%2C%20as%20they%20were%20anonymous%2C%20could%20become%20currency%20and%20undermine%20the%20faith%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20point%2C%20the%20RBI%20was%20unambiguous%3A%20amending%20the%20law%20to%20facilitate%20this%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20seriously%20undermine%20a%20core%20principle%20of%20central%20banking%20legislation%20and%20doing%20so%20would%20set%20a%20bad%20precedent%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20objection%20the%20RBI%20had%20was%20that%20%E2%80%9Ceven%20the%20intended%20purpose%20of%20the%20transparency%20might%20not%20be%20achievable%20as%20the%20original%20buyer%20of%20the%20instrument%20(bond)%20need%20not%20be%20the%20actual%20contributor%20to%20the%20party%E2%80%9D.%20If%20person%20A%20purchased%20the%20bond%20and%20then%20sold%20it%2C%20at%20face%20value%20or%20more%2C%20to%20any%20entity%2C%20including%20a%20foreign%20government%2C%20that%20entity%20could%20gift%20it%20to%20a%20party.%20The%20nameless%20bond%20was%20as%20good%20as%20cash.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20bonds%20are%20bearer%20bonds%20and%20transferable%20by%20delivery%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20RBI%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Chence%2C%20who%20finally%20and%20actually%20contributes%20the%20bond%20to%20the%20political%20party%20will%20not%20be%20known%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20point%20it%20made%20was%20that%20what%20was%20proposed%20through%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20%E2%80%94%20transfer%20of%20money%20from%20bank%20accounts%20of%20entities%20to%20political%20parties%20%E2%80%94%20could%20be%20done%20through%20a%20cheque%2C%20bank%20transfer%20or%20demand%20draft.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20special%20need%20for%2C%20or%20advantage%20by%2C%20the%20creation%20of%20an%20Electoral%20Bearer%20Bond%2C%20that%20too%20by%20disturbing%20an%20established%20international%20practice.%E2%80%9D%20The%20man%20charged%20with%20steering%20the%20thing%20through%20was%20Hasmukh%20Adhia%2C%20an%20IAS%20officer%20from%20Gujarat%20with%20a%20Ph.D.%20in%20yoga.%20(He%20had%20earlier%20chaperoned%20the%20GST%20Bill%2C%20and%20after%20he%20retired%2C%20was%20made%20chairman%20of%20the%20Bank%20of%20Baroda%20and%20chancellor%20of%20the%20Central%20University%20of%20Gujarat).%20He%20dismissed%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20objections%20on%20two%20grounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felectoral-bonds-fatf-report-bjp-constitution%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20Contrary%20to%20PMLA%2C%20Favours%20Ruling%20Party%E2%80%99%3A%20Coalition%20Report%20Tells%20FATF%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20appears%20the%20RBI%20has%20not%20understood%20the%20proposed%20mechanism%20of%20having%20pre-paid%20instruments%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20keeping%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20donor%20secret%2C%20while%20ensuring%20the%20donation%20is%20made%20only%20out%20of%20fully%20tax-paid%20money%20of%20a%20person.%E2%80%9D%20By%20this%20he%20meant%20because%20the%20original%20purchaser%20had%20to%20acquire%20the%20bonds%20through%20their%20official%20account%2C%20it%20made%20the%20donation%20clean.%20This%20was%20not%20a%20response%20to%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20specific%20objections.%20Adhia%20said%20the%2015-day%20time%20limit%20for%20redemption%20would%20mitigate%20against%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20other%20fears%2C%20without%20explaining%20how.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CAlso%20this%20advice%20has%20come%20quite%20late%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Finance%20Bill%20is%20already%20printed.%E2%80%9D%20It%20had%20actually%20come%20within%20hours%20of%20being%20sent%20for.%20It%20was%20hardly%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20fault%20that%20the%20advice%20had%20not%20been%20sought%20earlier.%20This%20was%20deceit%2C%20but%20Adhia%20concluded%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20may%2C%20therefore%2C%20go%20ahead%20with%20our%20proposal%E2%80%9D.%20His%20colleague%2C%20economic%20affairs%20secretary%20Tapan%20Ray%2C%20concurred%20with%20Adhia%20the%20same%20day%2C%20and%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20February%201%2C%20Jaitley%20announced%20the%20scheme%20which%20became%20law%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Union%20Budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAsked%20by%20journalist%20Nitin%20Sethi%20of%20Huffington%20Post%20(which%20carried%20a%20six-part%20investigation%20into%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20based%20on%20documents%20procured%20by%20RTI%20activist%20Commodore%20Lokesh%20Batra)%20why%20the%20government%20had%20ignored%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20objections%2C%20the%20finance%20ministry%20said%20it%20had%20taken%20the%20decision%20%E2%80%9Cin%20good%20faith%20and%20in%20the%20larger%20public%20interest%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20law%20was%20passed%2C%20the%20details%20were%20not%20made%20public.%20This%20came%20in%20June%202017%2C%20when%20Tapan%20Ray%20revealed%20how%20the%20bonds%20would%20work%20in%20practice%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20information%20regarding%20purchaser%20and%20payee%20shall%20be%20kept%20secret%20by%20the%20issuer%20bank.%20These%20details%20would%20be%20beyond%20the%20purview%20of%20RTI.%E2%80%9D%20(Ray%20was%20made%20chairman%20of%20the%20Central%20Bank%20of%20India%20after%20he%20retired%20in%202018%2C%20and%20in%202019%20was%20also%20made%20CEO%20and%20managing%20director%20of%20Gujarat%20International%20Finance%20Tec%20City.)%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20body%20to%20say%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20was%20dangerous%20was%20the%20Election%20Commission.%20In%20an%20affidavit%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20it%20said%20that%20to%20exclude%20the%20reporting%20of%20donations%20received%20by%20political%20parties%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20would%20have%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20repercussions%20on%20the%20transparency%20aspect%20of%20political%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%2C%20for%20six%20years%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20politics%20has%20been%20funded%20anonymously.%20It%20is%20time%20to%20end%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699354833000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F07155525%2FUntitled-design-5.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-two-ias-officers-chaperoned-the-electoral-bonds-bill-despite-rbis-objections%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20objections%20from%20the%20Election%20Commission%20too%2C%20for%20six%20years%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20politics%20has%20been%20funded%20anonymously.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A30%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-two-ias-officers-chaperoned-the-electoral-bonds-bill-despite-rbis-objections%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20The%20Who%E2%80%99s%20Who%20in%20the%20Data%20%7C%20Nai%2FHajjaam%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F07150202%2F6014608342_59791f2722_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBeyond%20politics%2C%20the%20Bihar%20caste%20survey%20is%20a%20revolutionary%20document.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20public%20document%2C%20the%20first%20ever%20after%201931%2C%20allowing%20for%20people%20to%20stand%20up%20and%20be%20counted.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20go%20down%20to%20the%20wire%2C%20on%20what%20each%20of%20the%20numbers%20unveiled%20mean.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWho%20are%20the%20people%20referred%20to%20by%20percentages%20in%20the%20survey%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EToday%20we%20look%20at%20Nai%20or%20Hajjaam%20(2%2C082%2C048%20people)%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECastes%20are%20not%20mere%20classification%20of%20the%20basis%20of%20labour.%20In%20western%20countries%2C%20members%20of%20the%20same%20family%20can%20opt%20for%20different%20professions%20and%20a%20single%20family%20can%20have%20cattle%20herders%2C%20carpenters%20and%20cobblers%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20But%20it%20is%20not%20so%20under%20the%20caste%20system.%20When%20professions%20are%20segregated%20into%20castes%2C%20social%20rules%20are%20imposed%20accordingly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20of%20the%20caste%20group%20we%20are%20talking%20about%20today%20can%20be%20found%20anywhere%2C%20be%20it%20a%20city%20or%20a%20village.%20They%20can%20be%20Hindu%20or%20Muslim.%20Among%20Muslims%20they%20are%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHajjaam%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20the%20work%20done%20by%20them%20is%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ehajamat%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20There%20are%20several%20names%20for%20them%20among%20Hindus%2C%20such%20as%20Nau%2C%20Naua%2C%20Kshaurik%2C%20Napit%2C%20Mundak%2C%20Bhandik%2C%20Nais%2C%20Sain%2C%20Sen%2C%20Savita-Samaj%2C%20Mangala%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20425px)%2085vw%2C%20425px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22425%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%20838w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-210x300.jpg%20210w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-715x1024.jpg%20715w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682410%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22609%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20caste%20group%20also%20has%20various%20names%20in%20different%20states.%20In%20Punjab%2C%20they%20are%20sometimes%20affectionately%20called%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Eraja%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fi%3Eor%20king.%20They%20are%20called%20Kulin%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Khawas%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20Sen%20Samaj%20or%20Napit%20in%20Haryana%2C%20and%20Nai-Thakur%20or%20Savita%20Samaj%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20people%20of%20this%20caste%20are%20responsible%20for%20cutting%20hair%20and%20grooming%20people.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Bihar%2C%20people%20of%20this%20caste%20are%20considered%20extremely%20backward.%20According%20to%20the%20caste-based%20survey%20report%20released%20by%20the%20Bihar%20government%2C%20their%20population%20in%20Bihar%20is%202%2C082%2C048%2C%20which%20is%20only%201.5927%25%20in%20terms%20of%20share.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Yet%2C%20this%20caste%20group%20has%20a%20special%20role%20in%20society%20and%20politics.%20As%20far%20as%20their%20social%20status%20is%20concerned%2C%20they%20are%20present%20in%20all%20important%20rituals%20in%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20life%2C%20from%20birth%20to%20death%2C%20along%20with%20people%20of%20the%20Brahmin%20caste.%20But%20they%20are%20not%20given%20the%20same%20respect%20as%20the%20Brahmins.%20In%20north%20India%2C%20there%20is%20a%20saying%20which%20derogatorily%20equates%20the%20Nai%20with%20a%20crow%20%E2%80%93%20a%20clever%20omnivorous%20bird.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20they%20are%20not%20untouchable%20because%20declaring%20them%20as%20such%20would%20cause%20discomfort%20to%20the%20people%20of%20this%20society%20who%20avail%20themselves%20of%20the%20services%20of%20this%20caste.%20Moreover%2C%20if%20someone%20wants%20to%20get%20shaved%2C%20they%20must%20allow%20the%20barber%20to%20touch%20their%20face.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20also%20a%20discussion%20in%20the%20Atharva%20Ved%20about%20%E2%80%9Cmaking%20them%20touchable.%E2%80%9D%20A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eshloka%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Esays%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20main%20person%20in%20the%20marriage%20ceremony%20is%20the%20barber%2C%20who%20finds%20a%20groom%20for%20the%20girl%20and%20verifies%20his%20qualifications.%20They%20perform%20key%20rituals%20and%20that%20is%20why%20they%20are%20the%20first%20ones%20to%20be%20entitled%20to%20wear%20Panchavastra.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20biggest%20contradiction%20in%20Indian%20society%20is%20that%20this%20essential%20labour%20too%20has%20been%20devalued.%20But%20if%20we%20look%20at%20the%20history%20of%20the%20development%20of%20human%20civilisation%2C%20perhaps%20the%20barber%20was%20the%20first%20person%20to%20have%20thought%20of%20grooming%20a%20person%20to%20make%20them%20look%20beautiful.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Historically%2C%20the%20period%20of%20emergence%20of%20barbers%20must%20have%20been%20after%20the%20Neolithic%20era%20when%20iron%20was%20discovered%20because%20scissors%20and%20other%20tools%20would%20not%20exist%20without%20iron.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20role%20of%20the%20barber%20community%20cannot%20be%20dismissed%20in%20the%20development%20of%20human%20civilisation.%20He%20was%20the%20first%20surgeon%20who%20used%20his%20tools%20to%20remove%20thorns%20from%20the%20feet%20of%20countless%20people%20and%20healed%20their%20wounds.%20Be%20it%20a%20king%20or%20a%20common%20man%2C%20barbers%20have%20served%20everyone%2C%20across%20caste%20groups%20too.%20Even%20today%2C%20in%20the%20villages%20of%20Bihar%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20women%20of%20the%20barber%20community%20serve%20women%20of%20all%20other%20castes%20%E2%80%93%20they%20clip%20nails%20and%20apply%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ealta%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20their%20feet%2C%20among%20other%20things.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%2C%20their%20wages%20were%20called%20%3Cem%3Ej%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Eajmanaka%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20They%20had%20a%20fixed%20share%20in%20every%20farmer%E2%80%99s%20household%20%E2%80%93%20one%20or%20two%20sacks%20of%20grains.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20despite%20being%20landless%2C%20the%20people%20of%20the%20barber%20community%20always%20had%20full%20barns.%20But%20now%20the%20era%20of%20j%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eajmanaka%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20gone.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20do%20business%20in%20cash%20now.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKarpoori%20Thakur%2C%20from%20the%20community%2C%20was%20a%20renowned%20politician%20of%20Bihar%20who%20became%20its%20chief%20minister%20twice.%20The%20recommendations%20of%20the%20Mungerilal%20Commission%20implemented%20by%20him%20gave%20an%20impetus%20to%20the%20politics%20of%20backward%20classes%20in%20the%20country.%20However%2C%20at%20present%2C%20it%20seems%20this%20community%20is%20in%20search%20of%20a%20hero%20for%20itself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F260208%2Fbihar-caste-survey-what-is-the-history-of-chaupal-caste%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20earlier%20parts%20of%20the%20series%20on%20the%20following%20communities%20by%20clicking%20on%20their%20names%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-ghasi%5C%22%3EGhasi%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3ESantrash%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3EMadaria%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-koeri-kushwaha%5C%22%3EKoeri%2FKushwaha%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chaupal%5C%22%3EChaupal%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20series%20is%20available%20in%20Hindi%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F260200%2Fbihar-caste-survey-who-are-the-santarash%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20in%20Urdu%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewireurdu.com%2Fauthor%2Fnaval-kishor-kumar%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699354475000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F07150202%2F6014608342_59791f2722_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-nai-hajjaam%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20biggest%20contradiction%20in%20Indian%20society%20is%20that%20essential%20labour%2C%20like%20that%20of%20barbers%2C%20too%2C%20has%20been%20devalued.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-nai-hajjaam%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Interview%20%7C%20Denied%20Ticket%2C%20BJP's%20Muslim%20Leader%20in%20Rajasthan%20Quits%20Party%20to%20Contest%20as%20an%20Independent%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F07145141%2FYunus-Khan.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Bhartiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20has%20not%20fielded%20even%20a%20single%20Muslim%20in%20any%20of%20the%20200%20Assembly%20constituencies%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20where%20elections%20will%20be%20held%20on%20November%2025.%20In%20the%202018%20elections%2C%20however%2C%20the%20party%20had%20fielded%20Yunus%20Khan%20of%20the%20Muslim%20community%20from%20the%20Tonk%20seat%2C%20which%20he%20lost%20to%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Sachin%20Pilot.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKhan%20had%20been%20MLA%20twice%20from%20Didwana%20before%20he%20contested%20and%20lost%20from%20Tonk%20in%202018.%20His%20hopes%20of%20obtaining%20a%20BJP%20ticket%20this%20time%20around%20from%20either%20Didwana%20or%20Tonk%20have%20been%20dashed%2C%20prompting%20him%20to%20quit%20the%20party%20and%20contest%20as%20an%20Independent%20candidate%20from%20the%20Didwana%20segment.%20He%20has%20been%20a%20close%20confidant%20of%20Vasundhara%20Raje%2C%20in%20whose%20government%20he%20served%20as%20transport%20minister%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20exclusively%20to%20Khan%2C%20and%20below%20are%20the%20excerpts%20from%20the%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%20%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20do%20you%20think%20the%20BJP%20has%20decided%20not%20to%20field%20you%20from%20either%20Didwana%20or%20Tonk%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20senior%20leadership%20not%20to%20give%20me%20a%20ticket.%20The%20party%20has%20done%20injustice%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Didwana%20by%20not%20giving%20me%20a%20ticket%2C%20as%20the%20people%20there%20wanted%20me%20to%20contest%20this%20election.%20This%20is%20the%20second%20time%20that%20the%20party%20has%20decided%20to%20ignore%20the%20wishes%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Didwana.%20Therefore%2C%20I%20have%20decided%20to%20contest%20from%20the%20constituency%20as%20an%20Independent%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDespite%20being%20known%20as%20a%20confidant%20of%20Vasundhara%20Raje%2C%20the%20party%20has%20denied%20you%20a%20ticket.%20In%20fact%2C%20several%20other%20leaders%20like%20Rajpal%20Singh%20Shekhawat%20from%20Jhotwara%20and%20Bhawani%20Singh%20Rajawat%20in%20Ladpura%20have%20been%20denied%20tickets.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20we%20three%20were%20denied%20tickets%20by%20the%20party%2C%20but%20many%20others%20who%20have%20been%20loyal%20to%20Raje%20didn%E2%80%99t%20get%20a%20ticket%20this%20time%3B%20Ashok%20Parnami%20is%20another%20example.%20Counting%20us%20in%20someone%E2%80%99s%20group%20is%20not%20the%20right%20thing%2C%20as%20we%20have%20been%20party%20workers%20for%20decades.%20We%20joined%20the%20BJP%20because%20we%20believed%20that%20the%20BJP%20was%20a%20party%20for%20change%2C%20and%20they%20also%20wanted%20to%20bring%20change.%20They%20gave%20tickets%20to%20candidates%20who%20joined%20the%20BJP%20in%202018%20and%20ignored%20loyalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20you%20not%20tried%20reaching%20out%20to%20Raje%20or%20any%20other%20leader%20in%20the%20BJP%20after%20you%20realised%20that%20you%20have%20not%20been%20given%20a%20ticket%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20from%20the%20BJP%20has%20ever%20contacted%20me%20after%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20loss%20in%202018%2C%20except%20former%20chief%20minister%20Vasundhara%20Raje.%20I%20have%20never%20demanded%20a%20ticket%20or%20anything%20from%20the%20party%20in%20the%20last%2025%20years.%20The%20party%20should%20have%20given%20tickets%20to%20winnable%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%202018%20too%2C%20we%20were%20not%20given%20the%20ticket%20from%20the%20seat%20of%20your%20choice%20(Didwana)%20and%20was%20shifted%20to%20Tonk.%20You%20were%20the%20only%20member%20of%20the%20Muslim%20community%20to%20have%20received%20a%20ticket%20back%20then%20among%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20candidates.%20Do%20you%20think%20your%20being%20a%20Muslim%20is%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20BJP%20denying%20you%20a%20ticket%3F%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20you%20should%20say%20that%2C%20as%20I%20have%20never%20done%20politics%20on%20religion.%20I%20have%20worked%20for%20the%20party%20for%20the%20last%2025%20years.%20It%20is%20for%20the%20media%20to%20analyse%20why%20the%20party%20has%20denied%20me%20a%20ticket%20this%20time%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20you%20not%20raised%20your%20concerns%20with%20Raje%20before%20deciding%20to%20quit%20the%20party%20and%20contest%20as%20an%20Independent%20candidate%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20have%20to%20listen%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Didwana%2C%20because%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20we%20are%20working%20for%20them%2C%20and%20the%20people%20want%20me%20to%20contest%20the%20elections%2C%20so%20I%20am%20contesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20think%20if%20the%20BJP%20comes%20to%20power%2C%20they%20will%20make%20Vasundhara%20Raje%20the%20chief%20minister%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20comment%20on%20it%2C%20as%20I%20left%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699353051000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F07145141%2FYunus-Khan.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Finterview-denied-ticket-bjps-muslim-leader-in-rajasthan-quits-party-to-contest-as-an-independent%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20transport%20minister%20and%20Vasundhara%20Raje's%20confidant%2C%20Yunus%20Khan%2C%20had%20hoped%20to%20contest%20on%20a%20BJP%20ticket%20from%20Didwana.%20However%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20not%20fielded%20even%20a%20single%20Muslim%20candidate%20from%20any%20of%20the%20200%20constituencies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Finterview-denied-ticket-bjps-muslim-leader-in-rajasthan-quits-party-to-contest-as-an-independent%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tearful%20mother%20describes%20how%20husband%20and%20son%20were%20taken%20hostage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699351500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F70x70%2Fskynews-batsheva-yahlomi-sky-news_6351455.jpg%3F20231107112935%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-hamas-war-tearful-israeli-mother-describes-how-she-escaped-hamas-capture-but-husband-and-son-were-taken-hostage-13002510%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20Israeli%20mother%20broke%20down%20in%20tears%20as%20she%20told%20how%20she%20and%20her%20daughters%20escaped%20capture%20by%20Hamas%20but%20her%20husband%20and%20son%20were%20taken%20hostage.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A852%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%